&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Senior Musculoskeletal Physiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part Time Post 22.5 Hours &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based at County Hospital Louth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and highly motivated Physiotherapist to this Band 6 MSK Physiotherapy post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join a small, friendly and supportive Physiotherapy team. Providing assessment and treatment within ULHT Therapy Services Outpatient Departments. Services are currently delivered at Louth &amp; Skegness Hospitals and within a GP surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have gained a broad range of postgraduate experience including recent work within the Musculoskeletal / Orthopaedic clinical area. You will be required to manage a caseload of musculoskeletal outpatients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your continuing development will be supported and developed by the Senior Physiotherapist within the clinical location and by the MSK Clinical Specialist.The team are provided with supervision and continuing CPD with monthly in service training .Opportunity to complete master modules at Lincoln University and shadowing local FCP services in the county are available.We support Physiotherapy student placements from local Universities .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
